    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Don't Give Up on Iraq</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Rob Scott letter holds that US should not pull out of Iraq short of victory</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''A Need for New Options on Iraq'' (letters, April 17):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''A Need for New Options on Iraq'' (letters, April 17):</p>
        <p>If the United States had withdrawn from World War II short of victory, what would the world be like today? Would we have the opportunity to be alive, and the liberty to wonder?</p>
        <p>If the United States pulls out of Iraq short of victory, what will the future hold for our children and grandchildren?</p>
        <p>These colors never run! The courage and valor of Omaha Beach and Iwo Jima run in the veins of our armed forces, who, even now, are fighting for freedom and a future free of fear.</p>
        <p>Rob Scott  Valley Stream, N.Y., April 17, 2007</p>
      </block>
